```cpp
#include <hexi/hexi.h>
#include <vector>
#include <string>
#include <cstdint>

struct NetworkPacket {
    uint32_t packet_id;
    std::string username;
    std::vector<uint32_t> scores;
    std::string metadata;

    void serialise(auto& stream) {
        // Write packet_id (arithmetic type, handled by operator<<)
        stream << packet_id;

        // Write username with prefix using prefixed adaptor
        stream << hexi::prefixed(username);

        // Write scores count (as arithmetic type) and then scores using operator<<
        // This will internally call write_container for the vector
        stream << static_cast<uint32_t>(scores.size());
        stream << scores;

        // Write metadata as null-terminated string using null_terminated adaptor
        stream << hexi::null_terminated(metadata);
    }
};

std::vector<uint8_t> serialize_packet(const NetworkPacket& packet) {
    // Create a buffer to hold the serialized data
    std::vector<uint8_t> buffer;

    // Create a buffer_adaptor for the buffer
    hexi::buffer_adaptor<std::vector<uint8_t>> adaptor(buffer);

    // Create a binary_stream with the buffer_adaptor
    hexi::binary_stream<decltype(adaptor)> stream(adaptor);

    // Call the serialise method on the stream with the packet
    stream.serialise(packet);

    // Return the buffer containing the serialized data
    return buffer;
}
```

## Explanation:

1. **`serialise` method implementation**:
   - `packet_id`: Written directly using `operator<<` since it's an arithmetic type
   - `username`: Uses `hexi::prefixed` adaptor which writes the length prefix followed by the string data
   - `scores`: First writes the count as arithmetic type, then uses `operator<<` which internally calls `write_container` for the vector
   - `metadata`: Uses `hexi::null_terminated` adaptor to write as null-terminated string

2. **`serialize_packet` function**:
   - Creates an empty `std::vector<uint8_t>` buffer
   - Creates a `buffer_adaptor` to interface with the buffer
   - Creates a `binary_stream` using the adaptor
   - Calls `serialise` on the stream with the packet
   - Returns the populated buffer

This implementation follows all the specified requirements and correctly uses the Hexi library's serialization functionality as described in the reference materials.

